Transactions are logged, and digital signatures captured for use in autogenerating documentation, such as form 0751. This lesson covers community and role responsibilities in the Asset Turn In process. For more information about the process, please go to Appendix A - Turn In Asset B

This lesson covers community and role responsibilities in the Asset Turn In process. Should any Role not have an individual provisioned in it, the Turn In process is not pressed correctly and the flow of the work order will stall. ## ROLE ## PERSON GROUPS Description ISO ISO Tech IMPORTANT! Local Site Support should be contacted if individuals need to be provisioned as required to allow a seamless flow of the Asset Turn In process. ## ASSET SANITIZATION CERTIFICATION (ISO) The Information Secu

Site Support should be contacted if individuals need to be provisioned as required to allow a seamless flow of the Asset Turn In process. ## ASSET SANITIZATION CERTIFICATION (ISO) The Information Security Officer must certify that Asset(s) marked as a Sensitive Item must have had all work completed prior to being picked up by PPM. Step 1. From the Inbox/Assignments portlet on the Start Center , select the appropriate Certify Sanitization of Assets on WO. Figure 1. Inbox/Assignments Portlet - Step 1. The Work Order opens in Work Order Tracking on the Work Order tab. Click the Route Workflow icon tool bar to accept responsibility. Figure 2. Route Work Flow Icon - Step 2. The Complete Workflow Assignment dialog box appears to Accept Responsibility to Certify Sanitization . Select the OK button. - Step 3. Scroll down to the Multiple Assets, Locations and CIs section. The Details section will display, and the icon will change to a Close Details . Review/verify the information in the Details section. Perform any physical validation needed on the assets listed. Repeat this for each item listed. NOTE: Values listed under Configuration Items are hard drives that have been removed and have had work performed on them. The 0751 will not be fully populated until certification is completed by the ISO. This report lists Configuration Items (hard drives) only and will not list the Assets. You will have one minute to answer the questions listed. You can use your user guide, if needed. Remember - you only have one minute. When I call 'Time,' we will review the answers. - 1. The ISO must be provisioned in Maximo? - a. Ture - b. False - 2. For assets requiring sanitization, the ISO must provide certification before it is picked up by PPM. - a. True - b. False - 3. The ISO can print the 0751 report. - a. Any time while on the work order - b. After certification to display all signature blocks are populated - c. Never - d. If the turn in request is not valid, proceedto step1.4.11. | | 1.4.3 | The Responsible Department(which may be FM, HTM, or IT) receives a work order and manually handles any necessarypre-turn in work if needed.Note:If the Responsible Department on the assets being turnedin is HTM or FMthenthe turn in work order will go to HTM or FMaccordingly. If the assets being turned in are on a 78 series EIL ANDif at least one of the assets on the work order is marked as a Sensitive Item, thenthe work order will go to IT. In any other cases, the work order will go directly to PPM. Note:If the Responsible Departmentof the asset(s) on the work order is HTM or FM, the HTM Admin or FMWO Cl

In any other cases, the work order will go directly to PPM. Note:If the Responsible Departmentof the asset(s) on the work order is HTM or FM, the HTM Admin or FMWO Clerk may first choose to delegate the work to and HTM Tech or an FM Tech. If the asset(s) on the work order are IT assets (on a 78 series EIL), the IT Tech will begin executionof any work needed. Examples of pre-turnin work include decontamination/wipe down of an asset, purging or removal of fluids, environmental management(such as cleaning hospital beds), ensuringsafe disposal of specialized assets (such as radioactive or other contaminates), cleaning lab equipmentcontaining reagents, removing freon from and defrosting refrigerators, uninstalling a piece of equipment. | | 1.4.4 | If the asset(s) onthe work order require data sanitization (e.g., removal of hard drives).
